onization that intensified after the 1832 Black Hawk conflict. Bringing together Native leaders, local residents, scholars, activists, and artists for a series of lectures, tours, and conversations, the seminar aims to understand the origins and effects of the present engineered landscape and build alliances for more just and sustainable futures.<\/p>\n","post_title":"Over the Levee, Under the Plow","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"over-the-levee-under-the-plow","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2020-06-03 16:05:19","post_modified_gmt":"2020-06-03 14:05:19","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":581,"guid":"http:\/\/cms.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/?post_type=project&#038;p=586","menu_order":0,"post_type":"project","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","author_name":"alan","permalink":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/project\/mississippi\/field-stations\/field-station-2-anthropocene-drift\/over-the-levee-under-the-plow\/","acf":{"thumbnail":{"ID":3900,"id":3900,"title":"PrairieSoy","filename":"PrairieSoy.jpg","filesize":391028,"url":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/PrairieSoy.jpg","link":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/project\/mississippi\/field-stations\/field-station-2-anthropocene-drift\/over-the-levee-under-the-plow\/prairiesoy\/","alt":"","author":"9","description":"by Ryan Griffis","caption":"","name":"prairiesoy","status":"inherit","uploaded_to":586,"date":"2019-08-24 13:10:16","modified":"2019-09-03 16:45:49","menu_order":0,"mime_type":"image\/jpeg","type":"image","subtype":"jpeg","icon":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-includes\/images\/media\/default.png","width":1500,"height":500,"sizes":{"thumbnail":"https:\/\/content.anthropocene-curriculum.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/PrairieSoy-768x256.jpg","thumbnail-width":768,"thumbnail-height":256,